[{"short_id":"gl8hqr","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gl8hqr","created_at":"2024-05-21T16:58:27.000-05:00","title":"When is foot fast, and when is it not?","url":"https://codeberg.org/dnkl/foot/wiki/Performance","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gl8hqr/when_is_foot_fast_when_is_it_not","submitter_user":"WilhelmVonWeiner","user_is_author":false,"tags":["linux"]},{"short_id":"wu1p2u","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wu1p2u","created_at":"2024-05-21T16:47:55.000-05:00","title":"How to write \"hookable\" software?","url":"","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"\u003cp\u003eDoes anybody have any resources/references/design patterns/guides/blog posts/etc for building software that is designed to be extensible by users?  I have a Kubernetes controller that I’d like to build in some user extension points for, and I’m not really sure the best way to go about this.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy rough requirements are\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUsers should be able to write in whatever language they want (or, at the \u003cem\u003every\u003c/em\u003e least, they shouldn’t have to recompile the controller binary)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eI guess I’d \u003cem\u003eprefer\u003c/em\u003e to avoid having a network call/grpc schema/whatever, but maybe that’s the most practical way to do this?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eI’d like a system that can potentially accommodate adding additional extension points in the future\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSecurity (for now) is a non-requirement, the people writing and running this code will already have cluster-admin access to the cluster, and there won’t be a way to accept untrusted code without the person with cluster-admin access approving it.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Does anybody have any resources/references/design patterns/guides/blog posts/etc for building software that is designed to be extensible by users?  I have a Kubernetes controller that I'd like to build in some user extension points for, and I'm not really sure the best way to go about this.\r\n\r\nMy rough requirements are\r\n\r\n1. Users should be able to write in whatever language they want (or, at the _very_ least, they shouldn't have to recompile the controller binary)\r\n2. I guess I'd _prefer_ to avoid having a network call/grpc schema/whatever, but maybe that's the most practical way to do this?\r\n3. I'd like a system that can potentially accommodate adding additional extension points in the future\r\n\r\nSecurity (for now) is a non-requirement, the people writing and running this code will already have cluster-admin access to the cluster, and there won't be a way to accept untrusted code without the person with cluster-admin access approving it.","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/wu1p2u/how_write_hookable_software","submitter_user":"drmorr","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","distributed","programming"]},{"short_id":"nwvr11","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nwvr11","created_at":"2024-05-21T16:03:22.000-05:00","title":"A history of a logo with a colon and two slashes","url":"https://daniel.haxx.se/blog/2024/05/21/a-history-of-a-logo-with-a-colon-and-two-slashes/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nwvr11/history_logo_with_colon_two_slashes","submitter_user":"eBPF","user_is_author":false,"tags":["historical"]},{"short_id":"vkxfqz","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vkxfqz","created_at":"2024-05-21T15:38:51.000-05:00","title":"What's new in Kotlin 2.0.0","url":"https://kotlinlang.org/docs/whatsnew20.html","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vkxfqz/what_s_new_kotlin_2_0_0","submitter_user":"asb","user_is_author":false,"tags":["kotlin","release"]},{"short_id":"glnsev","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/glnsev","created_at":"2024-05-21T15:15:16.000-05:00","title":"why is there so little of anything online about old phone UIs, firmwares and emulation?","url":"","score":5,"flags":0,"comment_count":5,"description":"\u003cp\u003ei had some pre-android phones, the ones that could run jar files and stuff. i really liked the gui systems on them. but i can’t find much about them online\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethere’s websites about old desktop UIs (\u003ca href=\"http://toastytech.com/guis/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttp://toastytech.com/guis/\u003c/a\u003e), modern recreations of their visuals (\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/themesberg/windows-95-ui-kit\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/themesberg/windows-95-ui-kit\u003c/a\u003e), old pc emulators (\u003ca href=\"https://infinitemac.org/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://infinitemac.org/\u003c/a\u003e), parodies (\u003ca href=\"https://www.windows93.net/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://www.windows93.net/\u003c/a\u003e), even some PDA emulators (\u003ca href=\"https://wuffs.org/WindEmu/index.html\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://wuffs.org/WindEmu/index.html\u003c/a\u003e), but nothing like that about phones? there are some emulators (\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/nikita36078/J2ME-Loader\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/nikita36078/J2ME-Loader\u003c/a\u003e), but afaik they are all just for running game executables and don’t emulate the full user-facing phone OS.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut it’s not like those mobile phones were than uncommon, it’s weird that i can’t find almost anything documenting or reviewing those UIs and OSes, i hope i’m just not googling it right. do you know of any resources about them?\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"i had some pre-android phones, the ones that could run jar files and stuff. i really liked the gui systems on them. but i can't find much about them online\r\n\r\nthere's websites about old desktop UIs (http://toastytech.com/guis/), modern recreations of their visuals (https://github.com/themesberg/windows-95-ui-kit), old pc emulators (https://infinitemac.org/), parodies (https://www.windows93.net/), even some PDA emulators (https://wuffs.org/WindEmu/index.html), but nothing like that about phones? there are some emulators (https://github.com/nikita36078/J2ME-Loader), but afaik they are all just for running game executables and don't emulate the full user-facing phone OS.\r\n\r\nbut it's not like those mobile phones were than uncommon, it's weird that i can't find almost anything documenting or reviewing those UIs and OSes, i hope i'm just not googling it right. do you know of any resources about them?","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/glnsev/why_is_there_so_little_anything_online","submitter_user":"two","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","historical","mobile"]},{"short_id":"oztrrs","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oztrrs","created_at":"2024-05-21T14:51:02.000-05:00","title":"I Connected My Farm to the Internet – Now What?","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bcDM6rTmEws","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oztrrs/i_connected_my_farm_internet_now_what","submitter_user":"hwayne","user_is_author":false,"tags":["api","hardware","video"]},{"short_id":"pkmqif","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pkmqif","created_at":"2024-05-21T14:42:33.000-05:00","title":"Stripe's monorepo developer environment","url":"https://blog.nelhage.com/post/stripe-dev-environment/","score":6,"flags":0,"comment_count":4,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/pkmqif/stripe_s_monorepo_developer_environment","submitter_user":"jez","user_is_author":false,"tags":["practices"]},{"short_id":"rqgglt","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rqgglt","created_at":"2024-05-21T14:29:52.000-05:00","title":"SpecLang","url":"https://githubnext.com/projects/speclang/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rq